Requirements 

4.1 Inputs (pipeline parameters) 

environment: dev | test | stage | prod 

namespace: e.g., dev-dethub 

releaseName: e.g., dethub 

chartVersion: e.g., 0.1.0 

Optional overrides:  

minio.rootPassword 

superset.init.adminUser.password 

superset-postgres.bootstrap.initdb.secret.name 

cn-postgres.bootstrap.initdb.secret.name 

dryRun: true/false 

rollbackOnFailure: true/false 

4.2 Secrets & Registries 

K8s secret: regcred-acr (for symphonyfs.azurecr.io) 

Azure ACR login/Helm repo auth via service connection 

App passwords: Provided via Key Vault or auto-generated by chart; if generated, persist back into K8s secrets. 

4.3 Endpoints & Security 

Public ingress: core-api, superset, minio 

Internal: Minio service, Kafka bootstrap, DB services 

RBAC: restrict who can run pipeline to a specific AAD group(s) 

4.4 Maintenance Rules 

If CNPG replicas = 1, remove PDB to avoid disruptions. 

Pod restarts are safe (no data corruption expected). 

Minimal pods for “up” state: core-db, core-api, superset-db, superset. 

