Deployment Flow 

Plan: resolve chart version, pull values, compute overrides. 

Pre‑checks: namespace exists, regcred-acr exists, PDB rule if CNPG=1, resource quota. 

Deploy: helm upgrade --install with version pin + values + overrides. 

Verify: kubectl rollout status, helm test, HTTP health checks. 

Report: publish logs, version, and summary. Optional Slack/Teams notify. 

Rollback Strategy 

If deploy fails and rollbackOnFailure=true, run:  

helm rollback <release> <revision-1> 

Re-verify; if still failing, auto‑pause and mark manual intervention required. 

Audit & Access 

Azure DevOps environment approvals for stage and prod. 

Pipeline permissions restricted to SCP-Deployers-DetectionHub AAD group. 

All operations logged; artifacts retained for 180 days. 

Acceptance Criteria 

One‑click deploy to dev succeeds with 0.1.0. 

Upgrade path validated (dev → test) with no downtime to minimal pod set. 

Rollback tested and functional. 

Documentation (this page + runbook) complete. 

 Risks 

Wrong PDB handling (single‑node CNPG) → rollout hang. 

Missing RBAC or service connections → pipeline failure. 

Helm chart breaking changes across versions → pin and test. 

